tive image builds. If Class.forName with sun.misc fails, it doesn’t progress to class$ in the native environment. It seems tests aren't asserting coverage in native, so I wonder if a dynamic-access report from the native compile would help. The goal is to improve dynamic-access coverage, so I might need to re-run the entire workflow to include coverage from the JVM, like JaCoCo.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Finalizing changes**\\n\\nI need to think through whether I added GetTest previously because it seems untracked in this turn, but the user might not have the latest version. The changes we made include the build.gradle file and GetTest. I want to avoid any contradiction regarding whether \\\"build.gradle is no longer modified.\\\" It’s essential to clarify this to ensure everything is accurate before finalizing the update. Let’s make sure I’ve got this correct!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented the coverage refinement for `org.apache.tools.ant.taskdefs.Get`.\n\nChanges made:\n\n- Added/refined `tests/src/ant/ant/1.6/src/test/java/ant/ant/GetTest.java`\n  - Exercises `Get.execute()` through its public API.\n  - Uses an in-memory `URLConnection`.\n  - Enables basic-auth handling with empty username/password so Ant’s fallback encoder remains safe.\n  - Verifies the downloaded content and `Authorization` header.\n\n- Updated `tests/src/ant/ant/1.6/build.gradle`\n  - Generates a tiny legacy `sun.misc.BASE64Encoder` class under `build/generated/legacyTestClasses`.\n  - Adds that directory to test output.\n  - Appends it to the JVM bootstrap class path for `Test` tasks.\n  - This allows Ant 1.6’s legacy auth path to find `sun.misc.BASE64Encoder`, proceed to `getMethod(\"encode\", new Class[] { byte[].class })`, and execute the remaining `Get.class$(Get.java:152)` dynamic-access call site.\n\nI did not run the tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_04424b36390761bc0169fc86bf58448190a9edaec3fe0f3455\",\"phase\":\"final_