rd. I also need to confirm that I can access org.apache.tools.ant.taskdefs.Get from the library. \\n\\nWith a custom URLClassLoader, can the call sites still reference the same class? I wonder if JaCoCo would handle this correctly. I just realized that a native image won't support dynamic loading of a jar after the build; however, if the classpath is known prior to the build, what could that mean for my setup?\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_aTUDIlpJLisxOf2smyX53OI7|fc_04424b36390761bc0169fc8769a5cc8190b6a672d41b099fbf", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/ant/ant/1.6/build.gradle", "edits": [{"oldText": "tasks.withType(Test).configureEach {\n    dependsOn generateLegacyBase64Encoder\n    jvmArgs '--add-opens=java.base/java.lang=ALL-UNNAMED'\n    doFirst {\n        jvmArgs \"-Xbootclasspath/a:${generatedLegacyClassesDir.get().asFile.absolutePath}\"\n    }\n}\n", "newText": "tasks.withType(Test).configureEach {\n    dependsOn generateLegacyBase64Encoder\n    jvmArgs '--add-opens=java.base/java.lang=ALL-UNNAMED'\n    doFirst {\n        jvmArgs '--add-modules=jdk.unsupported',\n                \"--patch-module=jdk.unsupported=${generatedLegacyClassesDir.get().asFile.absolutePath}\"\n    }\n}\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 495, "output": 1755, "cacheRead": 59904, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 62154, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778157393074, "responseId": "resp_04424b36390761bc0169fc875214108190a60882da78c005cb"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_aTUDIlpJLisxOf2smyX53OI7|fc_04424b36390761bc0169fc8769a5cc8190b6a672d41b099fbf", "toolName": "edit", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully replaced 1 block(s) in tests/src/ant/ant/1.6/build.gradle."}], "details": {"diff": "     ...\n  53 tasks.withType(Test).configureEach {\n  54     dependsOn generateLegacyBase64E